Utterance: Hi, Ellie!
Hi! It’s great to see you again. How have you been since our last session?
I’ve been doing well! I reached out to my brother, and we talked for a while.
That’s wonderful! How did that conversation go?
It was really nice. We caught up on everything, and it felt good to reconnect.
That’s fantastic! It sounds like you’re making progress in your family relationships. How did that make you feel?
It made me feel happy and relieved. I didn’t realize how much I missed talking to him.
That’s a beautiful realization. Have you noticed any changes in your mood since reaching out?
Yeah, I feel lighter, like a weight has been lifted off my shoulders.
That’s great to hear! It’s amazing how connection can impact our emotional well-being. How has work been for you?
Work has been busy, but I’m handling it better. I’ve been using my breaks to walk and breathe.
Excellent! It sounds like you’re really applying the coping strategies we discussed. Have you had any moments of pride at work lately?
Yes! I got recognized for my contribution to a project, and it felt really good.
That’s amazing! Celebrating those accomplishments is important. How did that recognition impact your confidence?
It boosted my confidence a lot. I feel like I’m really finding my place there.
That’s wonderful! As you continue to grow in your role, how do you plan to maintain that confidence?
I think I’ll keep reminding myself of my accomplishments and staying connected with my coworkers.
That’s a solid plan. Have you experienced any new challenges at work?
Just the usual stress, but I feel more equipped to handle it now.
That’s a great mindset to have. Have you been able to talk to anyone at work about your feelings?
I did! I spoke to a coworker about feeling overwhelmed, and they were really supportive.
That’s fantastic! It’s great to have that support system. How did that conversation impact your feelings?
It made me feel understood and less alone in my struggles.
That’s a powerful experience. Have you been able to implement any new strategies to manage your stress?
I’ve been trying to prioritize my tasks better and not take on too much at once.
That sounds like a wise approach. Setting boundaries is essential for maintaining balance. Is there anything else on your mind today?
I’ve been thinking about what I want to do next in my career.
That’s a significant topic. What are your thoughts?
I’m considering taking a writing class to expand my skills.
That’s a fantastic idea! Continuing to grow your skills can open up new opportunities. Would you like to set a goal for researching classes?
Yes, I’d like that.
Great! Let’s check in about that next time. How do you feel overall about your progress in therapy?
I feel like I’m making real changes, and it’s encouraging.
That’s wonderful to hear! Remember, progress takes time, and you’re doing great.
Thanks, Ellie. I appreciate your support.
You’re very welcome! I’m here to help. Let’s keep building on this momentum in our next session.
Sounds good!
Take care, and I look forward to seeing you again soon!
Bye!
